last_episode_to_air.name: The Inside Story
last_episode_to_air.overview: A submarine is trapped in an astonishing location. The Nektons launch an elaborate and dangerous rescue mission to save the people inside. Could it be their missing grandparents?

name: The Deep
overview: The adventures of the Nekton family, a family of daring underwater explorers who live aboard a state-of-the-art submarine, The Aronnax, and explore uncharted areas of the earth's oceans to unravel the mysteries of the deep.
tagline: The sea is deep and full of secrets

episodes.name: Here Be Dragons
episodes.overview: A dragon hunting expedition leads Ant to an ancient scroll that holds clues to an amazing mystery. But his family are trapped by the dragon and only Ant and Jeffrey can save them. And Jeffrey's a fish.

episodes.name: Dark Orca
episodes.overview: The Dark Orca pirates attack. They believe the Nektons have a rare treasure aboard their sub. With pirates on one side and an erupting undersea volcano on the other, the Nektons will have to get creative to escape.

episodes.name: A.I.M.Y.
episodes.overview: An artificial intelligence programmed to run the sub and protect the Nektons tries to stop their rescue mission because it's too risky. When they try to shut her down, she takes over completely to save them from themselves.

episodes.name: Digging Deeper
episodes.overview: Will and Ant are retrieving an item from the deepest part of the ocean, but it is not what they were told. They've been duped. And now there's a stowaway on the Aronnax, trying to take control of it.

episodes.name: Devil's Sea Mystery
episodes.overview: Are aliens stealing things from a Japanese island and dragging them underwater? Ant believes that's perfectly reasonable. The Nektons investigate and find something even more dangerous. But can they escape?

episodes.name: Lonesome Jim
episodes.overview: Someone just stole the rarest tortoise in the world and the Nektons are searching for it. But the man who stole it secretly wants to capture them too. They're walking into a trap, but really, there's no other way.

episodes.name: Captured
episodes.overview: Captain Hammerhead has captured the Nektons aboard his sub! But his rusty vessel is about to sink. The Arronax could save them all, but first, Hammerhead would have to free the Nektons-and that's not exactly in his character.

episodes.name: The Test
episodes.overview: To find a piece of the mysterious Ephemychron, the Nektons have to fight off whirlpools, zero visibility and giant robotic jellyfish. Is Nereus doing this to them? If not, who is really behind all these obstacles?

episodes.name: Fossil
episodes.overview: Huge prehistoric crocodiles still inhabit an underwater cave system the Nektons are exploring. Ant shouldn't have bonded with that baby croc-its enormous mother doesn't take kindly to kidnappers, and now she's after him.

episodes.name: Colossal Squid
episodes.overview: Ant and Fontaine hunt for one of the rarest ocean creatures: the colossal squid. But it turns out to be smarter than anyone thought and thinks the Nektons look tasty. Can the Aronnax survive being pulled down very, very deep?

episodes.name: Monster Hunter
episodes.overview: Media superstar Devil Daniels - Monster Hunter is hunting a sea creature that he believes is a menace, but the Nektons want to protect it. To make matters worse, the public are on Daniels's side.

episodes.name: The Phantom Sub
episodes.overview: Does a ghost sub haunt the ocean depths? Ant believes it does, but when he actually finds this "ghost sub", the truth is even stranger - and much more dangerous. Ant and Fontaine find themselves trapped - by a ghost?

episodes.name: The Abyss Stares Back
episodes.overview: While diving in a rare blue hole, a sinkhole in the middle of the sea, strange things begin to happen to the Nektons. They're seeing things that can't exist. And where did the exit go? Why is there no way out?

episodes.name: Junior Nektons
episodes.overview: Ant and Fontaine are sure they can control some young fans visiting the Aronnax. But when they have to rescue a whale calf, success depends on them and all the hyperactive kids working well together. What could go wrong?

episodes.name: Treasure of the Islanders
episodes.overview: Dolos has sold two maps leading to the same treasure: one to the Nektons, the other to the pirates. Now it's a race to get there first, and the winner will need to use every sneaky trick in the book to win.

episodes.name: Tunnel
episodes.overview: As the Nektons explore a mysterious tunnel behind a huge undersea waterfall, strange creatures and strong currents surprise them at every turn. Everything is not as it seems.

episodes.name: The Sunken Gallery
episodes.overview: The Nektons are arrested for stealing. Ant and Fontaine escape to prove their innocence, but whoever set them up is already two steps ahead.

episodes.name: Field of Giants
episodes.overview: Fontaine and Smiling Finn get stuck inside a giant clam as the Dark Orca pirates battle the Nektons for the giant pearl within.

episodes.name: The Proteus Factor
episodes.overview: Proteus, leader of the mysterious Guardians, traps the Aronnax in a magnetic field and kidnaps Ant, believing he is the key to finding Lemuria.

episodes.name: Song of the Siren
episodes.overview: Devil Daniels, Monster Hunter, attempts to hunt a siren - a mythical creature whose song lures sailors to their doom.

episodes.name: Bad Luck Fish
episodes.overview: A fish invades Jeffrey's home on the Aronnax. How can he get rid of it and its bad luck?

episodes.name: Strange Migration
episodes.overview: The Rover is swallowed by a huge prehistoric shark. Will and Fontaine manage to cling to its gills just inside its mouth.

episodes.name: Bloop
episodes.overview: The Nektons are trying to identify a unique life form. They've never seen it, they've only heard its sound: 'Bloop'.

episodes.name: The Twilight Zone
episodes.overview: A weird glowing fish has lured every fish in the area to its bioluminescence, and Kaiko and Will also fall under its spell.

episodes.name: Loki's Castle
episodes.overview: While fighting over Viking treasure, the Nektons take over the Dark Orca. But the pirates in turn take over the Aronnax.

episodes.name: Tartaruga
episodes.overview: The Nektons explore a floating island and find the final piece of the Ephemychron in a cave. But the island has a terrible secret.

episodes.name: From the Stars
episodes.overview: The Nektons try to stop a fallen satellite's fuel from polluting a marine sanctuary. But someone else is interested in the satellite.

episodes.name: The Baltic Sea Anomaly
episodes.overview: Is the Baltic Sea anomaly really a UFO that crashed into the ocean? Ant thinks it is. But what the Nektons find inside is even more strange.

episodes.name: Mermaids
episodes.overview: When Ant sees a mysterious creature swimming outside the Aronnax, he is determined to find out what it is, even when pirates get in his way.

episodes.name: Treacherous Waters
episodes.overview: The Nektons enter an area of the Bermuda Triangle where the laws of physics don't seem to apply. What's more, they can't escape.

episodes.name: Kenji's Monster
episodes.overview: A giant, upright creature, straight out of a monster movie, walks across the ocean floor, causing havoc.

episodes.name: Finn Comes Aboard
episodes.overview: Smiling Finn comes to the Nektons for help. He wants them to stop his father, Captain Hammerhead, from stealing a treasure.

episodes.name: Beware the Sentinels
episodes.overview: A mysterious ancient temple beneath the sea has been hidden for centuries. The Nektons discover it was hidden for a very good reason.

episodes.name: Hidden Secrets
episodes.overview: The Nektons' nemesis Alpheus Benthos breaks into the Aronnax to steal the Ephemychron and stop the Nektons from finding Lemuria forever. Ant is determined to get it back at all costs.

episodes.name: The Maze
episodes.overview: The Nektons find a mysterious underwater maze. When they enter it, walls shift and they become disoriented. They're soon trapped inside and, what's worse they're not alone.

episodes.name: Whale of a Tale
episodes.overview: The Nektons encounter a huge, white whale, but Devil Daniels: Monster Hunter is trying to capture it. When they discover who the whale really is, the Nektons go head-to-head with Daniels to save it.

episodes.name: The Missing
episodes.overview: The Nektons find the Dark Orca pirate submarine completely deserted. It's as if the pirate crew have abandoned it. But why? And what are those mysterious, ghostly sounds?

episodes.name: Thunder And Lightning
episodes.overview: At Catatumbo Bay, a lightning storm has been raging for hundreds of years, and for the first time, it's intensifying. The Nektons' investigations reveal that a gigantic creature is responsible.

episodes.name: The Gates
episodes.overview: When Alpheus Benthos announces he has found the gates to Lemuria, the Nektons fear he's beaten them to their greatest prize.

episodes.name: The Treasure
episodes.overview: The Dark Orca pirates unwittingly steal a treasure that could awaken a Monumential.

episodes.name: Off Line
episodes.overview: The Internet being down is the worst thing imaginable for Ant and Fontaine - until Ant finds the sea monster responsible for this. Can he save both?

episodes.name: Friends in Deep Places
episodes.overview: Trying to rescue Jess Gorman in an underwater cave proves dangerous for Ant and Fontaine until a manatee comes to their aid. But is it too late?

episodes.name: Just Eaten
episodes.overview: The Aronnax and Alpheus's sub are trapped within a giant jellyfish. They've been eaten and the jellyfish won't let food out.

episodes.name: Family Ties
episodes.overview: Devil Daniels insists he's relocating a dangerous killer whale. But it's a scam that turns dangerous. Our heroes need to save Ant and the whale.

episodes.name: The Circle Game
episodes.overview: The Nektons find an amazing underwater crop circle. It's been built by a giant male puffer fish to attract a mate. Can Ant help the romance along?

episodes.name: The Unicorn
episodes.overview: Ant tries to locate a 'diamond-horned sea-unicorn' as a present for Fontaine's birthday. But Dolos and Devil Daniels are also hunting it.

episodes.name: Purple Tide
episodes.overview: The Nektons try to save an island from the 'purple tide' that legend says will destroy everything. To save it, they need to locate the Protector.

episodes.name: The Race
episodes.overview: Ant wants to go faster than the fastest fish in the sea - the sailfish. But he hasn't counted on a deadly oil spill that threatens to destroy them.

episodes.name: Kidnapped
episodes.overview: Jeffrey is kidnapped, in his 'Jeffrey Knight', by Dark Orca pirates. Can Jeffrey turn the tables and save himself?

episodes.name: More Thunder and Lightning
episodes.overview: The Nektons return to the mysterious Lemurian Gates they found previously. Exploring within, they're stunned to discover Lemuria is here.

episodes.name: Lemuria
episodes.overview: The Nektons explore Lemuria but Fontaine realises the others are being affected by a dangerous algae. Can she find an antidote?

episodes.name: The Sceptre
episodes.overview: The Nektons find the Queen's sceptre. But faced with the Kraken and the Electric Ray Monumential together, can Ant make it work?

episodes.name: The Hole Truth
episodes.overview: Ant and Fontaine realise that their grandparents found Lemuria before them - but where are they now? The Nektons follow the trail they left but run into giant, predatory Sand Strikers. Was this the fate of their grandparents?

episodes.name: The Biggest
episodes.overview: Ant searches a deep chasm for clues to his grandparents' fate but is stunned to find Mad Madeline there. She has been looking for the biggest sunken treasure ever, but all she has managed to find is the biggest monster.

episodes.name: Little Problems
episodes.overview: Three baby Monumential turtles hatch, and they are the size of city blocks. The playful babies accidentally sink a fishing trawler. Can the Nektons wrangle these creatures before they sink even more ships?

episodes.name: The Lead
episodes.overview: Does Dolos really have a lead on finding Ant’s grandparents? Or is he leading the Nektons into a dangerous chasm between moving tectonic plates for nefarious purposes?

episodes.name: AWOL
episodes.overview: A mysterious dolphin in a sophisticated electronic harness zaps all the Rover's power. Ant and Fontaine manage to remove the harness, but can they rehabilitate this cybernetic dolphin to survive in the wild?

episodes.name: Deceptive Appearances
episodes.overview: Mad Madeline steals the dangerous Sceptre of Queen Dorius.

episodes.name: Glass Houses
episodes.overview: The Nektons help locate a legendary Singaporean glass cabinet. However, they discover it is guarded by a terrifying and familiar creature.

episodes.name: Unidentified Floating Objects
episodes.overview: The Nektons are busy recovering sunken shipping containers, so when Bethany the fish finds herself in danger, only Jeffrey can save her.

episodes.name: At the Bottom of the Gyre
episodes.overview: Ant has created a clever machine to clean up a vast oceanic rubbish dump. However, when the machine is been eaten by a huge creature, it's up to the Nektons to save it.

episodes.name: Walking with Fish
episodes.overview: Ant and Fontaine discover the secret of the Bajau Laut people, a tribe of sea nomads living in the South China Sea. The pair are determined to help them - but how do you find a fish that walks?

episodes.name: Getting Warmer
episodes.overview: Ant and Fontaine rescue a polar bear from the middle of the ocean. However, when they bring her onboard, they realize she is close to giving birth. Can the Nektons move her to a safer place in time?

episodes.name: The Big Clue
episodes.overview: Fontaine is amazed when Smiling Finn tells her that he has detected a signal from her grandparents’ missing submarine. Is this a joke, an elaborate scam, or something even more amazing?

episodes.name: The Inside Story
episodes.overview: A submarine is trapped in an astonishing location. The Nektons launch an elaborate and dangerous rescue mission to save the people inside. Could it be their missing grandparents?
